# UDS Site Changelog

Whenever you modify ANY file in `uds-docs/`, you MUST perform these three steps before completing the task:

## 1. Bump the SITE version

**Run `bash uds-docs/bump-site.sh`** — this handles everything:
- Gets today's date from the system `date` command (NEVER guess)
- Increments N if same day, resets to `.1` if new day
- Updates all 3 locations: index.html display, index.html inline SITE_VERSION, version.txt

NEVER manually edit the version string. ALWAYS use the script.

## 2. Add a SITE_CHANGELOG entry

After the repo restructure, the SITE changelog lives at
`uds-docs/docs/data/site-changelog.js` (no longer inside `app.js`). Find
the `SITE_CHANGELOG` array and **append** a new entry for the current SITE
version (newest entries go LAST in the array — the renderer reverses for
display):

```javascript
{
  version: 'SITE YYYY.MM.DD.N',   // matches the version in index.html
  date: 'YYYY-MM-DD',
  changes: [
    { type: 'added|changed|fixed|removed', text: 'Description of what changed' }
  ]
}
```

- If you're making multiple changes in one session, batch them into a single version entry
- If an entry for the current version already exists, append to its `changes` array
- Types: `added` (new feature/page), `changed` (modification), `fixed` (bug fix), `removed` (deletion)

## 3. Cache busting

Three things to update:

### a. Query params on script/link tags in `index.html`:
- `<link rel="stylesheet" href="./uds/uds.css?v=N" />` — bump if any CSS changed
- `<script src="./uds/uds.js?v=N"></script>` — bump if any JS changed
- `<script type="module" src="./docs/app.js?v=N"></script>` — bump if `docs/app.js` (or anything it imports) changed
- `<script type="module" src="./docs/modules/demo-builder/index.js?v=N"></script>` — bump if any Demo Builder module changed
- `<link rel="stylesheet" href="./docs/site.css?v=N" />` — bump if `docs/site.css` changed

Only bump the ones where the underlying file actually changed.

### b. Update `version.txt`:
Write the new SITE version number (just the `YYYY.MM.DD.N` part, no `SITE` prefix) to `uds-docs/version.txt`. This file is fetched on every page load to trigger auto-reload when a new version is deployed.

### c. Update the inline SITE_VERSION in `index.html`:
Find the `var SITE_VERSION = '...'` string in the inline `<script>` block in `<head>` and update it to match the new version.

## Exceptions

- Do NOT create a site changelog entry for changes that ONLY affect files outside `uds-docs/` (e.g. editing Cursor rules)
